    <string name="login_instructions_toggle_hide">Setup Instructions ▲</string>
    <string name="login_instructions_text"><![CDATA[1. Create new account at e-mail service supporting IMAP/SMTP (Gmail, Outlook, Yandex, Mail.ru, Yahoo! etc). These services don\'t support IMAP: Tuta, ProtonMail.\n\n2. Enable access from mail clients (IMAP/POP3/SMTP) in your mail settings.\n\n2.1. Google.\nOpen email in browser, select Settings - See all settings - Forwarding and POP/IMAP\na. Enable POP (any of two options).\nb. When a message is marked as deleted and expunged from the last visible IMAP folder: Immediately delete the message forever.\n\n2.2. Yandex.\nOpen email in browser (for mobile, switch to full version), select Settings - All settings - Email clients.\na. Use a mail client to retrieve your Yandex mail: From the imap.yandex.com server via IMAP\n\n3. Get an app password for IMAP and SMTP servers.\n\nNote: to generate app password all these services require to enable two-step auth via phone/sms (to ensure your security OF COURSE).\n\na. Gmail: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords\nb. Yandex: https://id.yandex.ru/security/app-passwords\nc. Mail.ru: https://account.mail.ru/user/2-step-auth/passwords]]></string>

